<title>USA: N.Y. official sees state power agency inefficiency.</title>
<headline>N.Y. official sees state power agency inefficiency.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-09-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>New York Power Authority's (NYPA) nuclear and fossil fueled generation operations could lose $2 billion by 2004 if it does not boost efficiency, New York state comptroller Carl McCall said Monday.</p>
<p>&quot;The financial losses at NYPA's non-hydroelectric operations raise questions about the benefit of NYPA's continued operation,&quot; McCall said in a statement based on an audit of NYPA management and operations.</p>
